IBADAN – The Chairman of a foremost Pan-Yoruba Intelligentsia Group, Voice of Reason (VOR), Dr Olufemi Adegoke, is dead. The late Adegoke was the father of Nigerian born member of the British Parliament, Olukemi Olufunto Adegoke, Badnock, a member of the Conservative Party, who has served in Boris Johnson’s government as Minister of State for Levelling Up Communities and Minister of State for Equalities. In a statement by Communications Secretary, Ilana Omo Oodua Worldwide, Maxwell Adeleye on Friday stated that Dr Olufemi Adegoke was a man of unquestionable character and a man whose lifestyle was a model. Ukrainian President Downplays Talk Of Russian Invasion 10 Injured In Pittsburgh Bridge Collapse He was resolute and committed toward the complete decommissioning of the 1999 Constitution of Nigeria. Adegoke spent his last years on the surface of the earth working for the advancement and liberation of the Yoruba people. He was an unparalleled patriot of the Yoruba people and an Intellectual Giant whose courage and candour goes beyond the cosmos. The late Olufemi Adegoke, a Medical Veteran, hailed from Ondo Town in Ondo West Local Government Area of Ondo-State. The Alana of Ilana Omo Oodua Worldwide, Professor Banji Akintoye and all the Yoruba Self-determination Soldiers within and beyond the shores of Yoruba Land sympathises with the Adegoke’s clan Worldwide on this irreparable loss of their Patriarch and wish them the fortitude to bear the loss.